    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Being Mark Twain</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>David Hawkins letter notes that Hal Holbrook has been Mark Twain longer than Samuel Langhorne Clemens was (Feb 14 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Holbrook's Half Century as Twain: An Actor Never Tires of Channeling an Ornery, Irresistible Spirit'' (Arts pages, Feb. 13):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Holbrook's Half Century as Twain: An Actor Never Tires of Channeling an Ornery, Irresistible Spirit'' (Arts pages, Feb. 13):</p>
        <p>Hal Holbrook's half century as Mark Twain means that he has been Mark Twain longer than Samuel Langhorne Clemens was.</p>
        <p>DAVID HAWKINS  Brooklyn, Feb. 13, 2003</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
